  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Awareness and protection of older women and men against Covid-19 in the Gaza strip</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will prioritize a prevention, awareness raising and community sensitization focus, that will help mitigate the impact of a COVID-19 outbreak when it materializes. It has a particular focus on vulnerable groups of older women and men and persons with disabilities. The project involves community awareness raising activities, which will be delivered through a mix of messaging modalities, such as radio spots, mobile text messages, use of social media and distribution of leaflets. For households which include an older woman or man, who are deemed particularly vulnerable, we will deliver hygiene kits for family use, and this distribution will also be accompanied by appropriate messaging and delivery of information. In addition, we will conduct medical diabetes and hypertension tests for older people by relevant health workers. We will set up a system to ensure the maintenance of social contact with older people who might be isolated using phone calls, text messages and radio. We will also ensure that provision of awareness raising and information on COVID-19 is made accessible to different groups of people, including older people, through appropriate language, communication materials and age relevant messaging.</narrative>
  </description>
